item.description: On this page, we’re collecting all articles and video tutorials we can find regarding Learning machine learning with ML.Net It is updated on a daily basis What is ML.Net? ML.Net is the open source machine learning framework for .Net, created and used internally by Microsoft Open source Highly performant Cross platform Completely in .Net Runs TensorFlow models Runs and saves ONNX models You can find the page at Microsoft And the repository at GitHub

item.title: Datasets
item.description: Where to find data to train on? Here is a collection of pages you can find data sets on kaggle UCI machine learning repository

item.title: Laptop prices data set
item.description: The Laptop price data set Dataset of prices on used laptops based on their specifications. Collected by Karl Tillström in 2020 File download LaptopPrices Contents Columns are tab separated Input Columns: CPU GHz GPU RAM RAMType Screen Storage SSD Weight Price Output column: Price (in USD) Usage If you use it; give credit by linking to https://www.machinelearningfordevelopers.com/datasets/laptopprices License: CC BY 4.0 You are free to: Share — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material for any purpose, even commercially.

item.title: Meerkat VS mere cat data set
item.description: The Meerkat VS Mere cat dataset This data set contains images of cats and meerkats for use in image classification training. The Images are collected in 2020 by www.machinelearningfordevelopers.com File download Meerkat VS merecat dataset All images are from Unsplash.com and is subject to their License License All photos published on Unsplash can be used for free. You can use them for commercial and noncommercial purposes. You do not need to ask permission from or provide credit to the photographer or Unsplash, although it is appreciated when possible.
